info.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 28 at 12:54PM AKST until January 29 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 6 AM AKST MONDAY... * WHAT...Southeast winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 65 mph expected. * WHERE...Craig, Hydaburg, Ketchikan, and Metlakatla. * WHEN...From 6 PM Sunday to 6 AM AKST Monday. * IMPACTS...High winds will blow around unsecured objects and may damage property and cause power outages. Travel will be difficult. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...As of early this afternoon, wind gusts have increased to 25 mph. WInds and wind gusts will continue to steadily increase through the afternoon.
info.instruction: People are urged to secure vessels and loose objects that could be blown around or damaged by the wind. Report any damage to the National Weather Service by visiting weather.gov/Juneau/StormReports
